comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T17:45:24.101Z",codex-agent,"Related SDK evidence: this PR does not complete the CLI namespace consolidation, but it preserves package vocabulary in the SDK via PmClient.package and top-level packageLifecycle helpers while exposing package install/uninstall/doctor/manage/describe/reload/catalog/activate/deactivate/upgrade primitives. pm-tnud remains open because hidden alias shims, CLI full verb parity, contracts/MCP/completions regeneration, and install/upgrade alias specs are still outstanding."
  "2026-07-07T18:07:11.560Z",codex-agent,"Bundle note: SDK package lifecycle helpers now preserve package vocabulary in PmClient.package(...) even if caller options include a conflicting vocabulary value; this supports package namespace consistency while broader CLI namespace consolidation remains open."
  "2026-07-22T06:10:48.766Z",codex-root-20260722,"Dogfood finding from PR #643 (duplicate-safe reuse): unversioned pm install npm:pm-changelog --project preserved the existing managed 2026.7.18 package even after npm latest advanced to 2026.7.22, while a fresh CI checkout installed 2026.7.22. Explicit npm:pm-changelog@2026.7.22 upgraded correctly. The consolidated pm package install/upgrade surface should make current-versus-latest visible and give agents an explicit idempotent refresh path; this belongs to the existing pm-tnud lineage, not a duplicate item."
body: ""
